            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked through, remove the pan from the heat and stir through a large knob of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>Jamaican-style jumbo prawn curry</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a fork and add it to a large bowl with the <strong>chopped pineapple</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> pineapple rice</strong></p>",
